{
  "stem": "13063.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Extremely husky man, tall, you know, and with the German boots, with a-- with a whip in his hand, and a gun, of course.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The gun was mostly in his hands.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But usually, he has-- he had both the gun and-- and the-- and the whip in his-- in his hands, in one hand and the other.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had three dogs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he kept the dogs just to-- to be able to-- to wound or kill for his own pleasure.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One dog was named Rolf, R-O-L-F.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a-- a killer like himself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He used to incite the-- the dogs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if-- if he didn't like somebody, instead of killing him by a-- by a gun, he wanted to see him torn by the dog.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think I saw it once, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Faintly, faintly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember it faintly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know that the dog-- the dog was-- had-- had a-- big, a big dog with-- with white with-- he looked like a dalmatian, but really, it was more than a dalmatian.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was some-- some-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he had black spots, as I remember, the dog, one of them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had three, of course.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One was a German shepherd.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But of course, the-- Amon Goeth's story and history is well-- very well documented in the film and also in Keneally's book.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Goeth, Amon Goeth?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sure, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He shot our-- you see, every barracks-- we were in-- in barracks in the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every barrack had a-- a-- a-- a-- somebody who-- who was responsible for-- for-- for cleanliness, for-- for discipline, and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Goeth came in once one-- one morning, and he found something irregular, something irregular.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He says, who is-- who is responsible?",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
